我得先考虑爱荷华州
I need to get through Iowa first.

61
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:49,270
我要推荐个人  先生  那人不在名单上
Well, I have a suggestion, sir, that's not on the list.

62
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:50,030
谁
Who?

63
00:02:50,890 --> 00:02:51,510
我
Me.

64
00:02:53,610 --> 00:02:55,910
赛斯  作为新闻主管  你的价值无法估量
Seth, you're invaluable as a comm director.

65
00:02:55,910 --> 00:02:57,310
就是因为这个  先生
Well, that's just it, sir.

66
00:02:57,530 --> 00:02:59,270
您需要个媒体专家替您掌舵
You need a media expert at the helm.

67
00:02:59,270 --> 00:03:00,310
我们处在选举周期之内呢
We're in an election cycle.

68
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:02,010
-一切都和公共形象密切相关  -赛斯
- Everything's about perception. - Seth--

69
00:03:02,010 --> 00:03:04,140
我想将政策和新闻团队完美融合
I want to integrate the policy and the press teams.

70
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:06,120
我希望与内阁成员及机构首脑合作
I want to work with cabinet members and agency heads

71
00:03:06,130 --> 00:03:09,120
按我们的政纲调整每份公开声明
on gearing every public statement towards our platform.

72
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:11,610
动员国会中的《美就法》盟友
Mobilize our AmWorks allies in Congress.

73
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:13,090
一份关于未来立法的承诺表
A commitment list for future's legislations,

74
00:03:13,090 --> 00:03:14,640
不仅是支持
not just simple endorsements.

75
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:16,240
这里面详细写了
Look, this outlines in detail

76
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:18,880
我担任您幕僚长会采取的行动
what I would like to do as your Chief of Staff.

77
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:21,950
我只求您考虑考虑
All I ask is that you consider it.

78
00:03:21,950 --> 00:03:24,470
我当然会的  谢谢你  赛斯
Well, of course I will. Thank you, Seth.

79
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:26,560
我很感激你这么花心思
I appreciate you putting so much time into this.

80
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,410
谢谢您  先生
Thank you, sir.

81
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:33,900
谢谢
Thank you.

82
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,120
罗伯特
Robert.

83
00:03:36,970 --> 00:03:38,310
抱歉我来晚了
Sorry I'm running late.

84
00:03:38,780 --> 00:03:40,560
我们从爱荷华州回来时天气不太好
We hit some weather on the way back from Iowa.

85
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:42,490
我感谢你亲自过来
I appreciate your coming here in person.

86
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:45,320
尤其在这...最后冲刺阶段
Especially during the... final rush.

87
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:47,620
为了你什么都行  罗伯特
Anything for you, Robert.

88
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:48,390
请坐
Have a seat.

89
00:03:48,390 --> 00:03:49,360
多谢
Oh, thank you.

90
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:53,180
这也好  我也能跟孩子们待一会儿
And, you know, it's good. I get a few hours with the kids.

91
00:03:54,410 --> 00:03:56,250
回到这儿感觉如何
So how does it feel to be back here?

92
00:03:59,290 --> 00:04:01,270
我得承认  我是有点怀念
I have to admit, I miss it a little.

93
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:05,230
顺说  你戈弗雷诉肯特案的异议提得真好
Your dissent on Godfrey v. Kent was brilliant, by the way.

94
00:04:07,780 --> 00:04:10,440
我的手下  是他们写的
My clerks. They wrote it.

95
00:04:11,130 --> 00:04:12,150
每个字都是
Every word.

96
00:04:14,970 --> 00:04:16,050
所以现在是时候了
So it's time.

97
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:19,590
露丝说是  但我在她开口前就知道了
Ruth says it is, but I knew before she said anything.

98
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,610
-你准备什么时候宣布  -很快
- When are you going to announce? - Soon.

99
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:27,680
但是我想先听你说同意
But I'd like you... to say yes first.

100
00:04:28,150 --> 00:04:29,890
-同意什么  -接替我
- To what? - Replacing me.

101
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,990
我并不是病糊涂了
This isn't the disease speaking.

102
00:04:35,990 --> 00:04:38,480
我并没有忘记你正在竞选总统
I haven't forgotten you're running for President.

103
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,930
但是安德伍德
But Underwood...

104
00:04:40,570 --> 00:04:44,430
我肯定他会毫不犹豫地同意提名你
I'm sure he'd nominate you in a heartbeat.

105
00:04:44,510 --> 00:04:47,580
我现在占上风  罗伯特  为什么要退出
I am the frontrunner, Robert. Why would I drop out?

106
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:49,040
因为这个职位是终身的
Because this position's for life.

107
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,580
安德伍德会输的
Underwood is going to lose.

108
00:04:50,580 --> 00:04:53,150
你觉得他会轻易认输吗
You think he'll go down easily?

109
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:56,210
而且即使你拿到了提名  共和党...
And even if you get the nomination, the Republicans...

110
00:04:57,330 --> 00:05:00,030
他们会生吞活剥了你
They'll... rip you apart.

111
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:04,930
我是决定性一票  我的位置很重要
I'm the swing vote. My seat is important.

112
00:05:04,930 --> 00:05:08,260
你在这里可以产生长期的影响
You can make a lasting difference here.

113
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:10,930
他也是这么说的
That is exactly what he said.

114
00:05:10,930 --> 00:05:13,830
他的动机不纯  是的
His motivations were atrocious, yes,

115
00:05:13,830 --> 00:05:16,710
但他说的道理是对的
but his logic was sound.

116
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:20,550
看来你的头脑还像过去一样清醒  罗伯特
Your mind seems sharp as ever, Robert.

117
00:05:21,670 --> 00:05:22,480
只是
Except...

118
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:28,960
只是我现在想不起来你叫什么
Except for the fact that I can't remember your name right now.

119
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:31,230
希瑟
Heather.

120
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,220
希瑟
Heather.

121
00:05:37,890 --> 00:05:41,650
你能继续我未竟的事业吗  希瑟
Will you continue to do the work I've done, Heather?

122
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:42,700
我不能
I can't.

123
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:46,700
摸着良心说  我太希望能成功了
If I'm honest with myself, it's that I want this too much.

124
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:49,170
开始竞选前我根本没有意识到
I didn't realize it before I started running.

125
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:51,020
并不是我变了  罗伯特
It is not that I've changed, Robert,

126
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:53,500
我并不是被野心蒙蔽了双眼
that ambition has clouded anything.

127
00:05:53,540 --> 00:05:57,070
而是我之前都没有意识到我注定该做什么
It is that I was blind to this until now, what I am meant to be.

128
00:05:57,300 --> 00:06:00,770
我注定要成为美国总统
And I am meant to be President of the United States.

129
00:06:29,690 --> 00:06:32,650
你们是不是都想先听克莱尔讲话
Wouldn't you all like to hear from Claire first?

130
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,170
谢谢
Thank you!

131
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:46,150
弗兰西斯和我十分感激你们能冒着严寒
Francis and I so appreciate you all coming out here

132
00:06:46,150 --> 00:06:49,510
到这里来如此热情地欢迎我们
on such a cold day and welcoming us with such warmth!

133
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:51,600
回到爱荷华真是太好了
It's so good to be back in Iowa!

134
00:06:56,750 --> 00:07:00,180
而且我能感觉到  有了你们的支持和热情
And I can feel it, with your support and enthusiasm,

135
00:07:00,180 --> 00:07:03,120
我们毫无疑问会拿下这个州
there is no doubt that we are gonna take this state!

136
00:07:09,410 --> 00:07:10,430
-你好  -晚上好
- Hello. - Good evening.

137
00:07:12,050 --> 00:07:14,530
很高兴二位又能在我家留宿  总统先生
So pleased to have you staying with us again, Mr. President.

138
00:07:14,530 --> 00:07:16,380
我们一向喜欢来这里
We always love coming here.

139
00:07:16,730 --> 00:07:18,570
这是全爱荷华我们最喜欢的房子
It's our favorite house in all of Iowa.

140
00:07:18,910 --> 00:07:21,240
-如果二位有什么需要  -非常感谢
- If you need anything... - Thank you very much.

141
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,350
-晚安  -祝你们睡个好觉
- Good night. - Have a good evening.

142
00:07:34,130 --> 00:07:35,850
你今天表现十分出色
You were wonderful today.

143
00:07:36,970 --> 00:07:38,400
他们非常喜欢你
They just adore you.

144
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:41,170
晚安
Good night.

145
00:07:43,950 --> 00:07:44,830
晚安
Good night.

146
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,060
请帮我接通汤姆·耶茨的电话
Yes, connect me with Tom Yates, please.

147
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,640
不  我等着
No, I'll hold.

148
00:09:01,820 --> 00:09:03,050
总统先生
Mr. President?

149
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,700
剩下的部分呢
Where's the rest of it?

150
00:09:05,510 --> 00:09:06,880
-你读了吗  -还没有
- Have you read it? - No, not yet.

151
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,620
我只拿到了第一章
Just this first chapter arrived.

152
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:11,940
请你先读一下  先生  然后我们再谈
Will you please read it first, sir? And then let's talk.

153
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:13,570
你病了吗  你的声音有点哑
Are you sick? You sound hoarse.

154
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:14,760
没有  我没生病
Well, no, I'm not sick.

155
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:16,610
只是缺觉而已
I haven't slept much.

156
00:09:16,770 --> 00:09:18,140
好吧  我明天再给你打电话
All right, I'll call you tomorrow.

157
00:09:21,580 --> 00:09:22,350
先生
Sir?

158
00:09:23,050 --> 00:09:24,220
不好意思  先生
Excuse me. Sir?

159
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:27,230
我忘了我进来干什么了
I forgot why I came in here.

160
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,850
那瓶橙汁
The orange juice.

161
00:09:32,770 --> 00:09:34,190
2美元25美分
That'll be two twenty-five.

162
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:36,820
好的
Yeah.

163
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:56,460
"国庆节已经变得毫无意义
"The Fourth of July means nothing anymore.

164
00:09:57,460 --> 00:09:59,190
烤焦的热狗
Overcooked hot dogs

165
00:09:59,190 --> 00:10:02,280
永远令你失望的焰火
and fireworks that always leave you disappointed.

166
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:04,970
中国制造的小号美国国旗
Bite-size American flags made in China,

167
00:10:05,020 --> 00:10:07,120
在一心只想去打游戏的五岁顽童
halfheartedly waved by five-year-olds

168
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:09,150
手中有一搭没一搭地挥舞着
who'd rather be playing Minecraft.

169
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:14,430
但9月3日  却是真正重要的一天
But the third of September, that's a date which matters.

170
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,890
三十年前的这一天
It's the day, three decades past,

171
00:10:17,990 --> 00:10:21,660
一个加夫尼的农民娶到了一位达拉斯的名媛
that a redneck from Gaffney married a debutante from Dallas.

172
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:25,500
世界旋转的角度在那天改变了
And the Earth's axis tilted that day,

173
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:29,390
尽管当时他们  以及我们都并不知道
though neither they, nor we, knew it at the time.

