00:29:29,390 --> 00:29:30,650
祝你好运  苏茜
Good luck to you, Suzie.

525
00:29:36,470 --> 00:29:38,480
安德伍德夫人  她改主意了吗
Mrs. Underwood, did she change her mind?

526
00:29:38,630 --> 00:29:40,310
没有  她坚持己见
No, she stuck to her guns.

527
00:29:40,310 --> 00:29:42,550
但你不能怪一个女人坚持信念
But you can't blame a woman for having conviction.

528
00:29:44,560 --> 00:29:45,780
总统刚刚打来找您
The president just called for you.

529
00:29:45,780 --> 00:29:47,110
我上车后给他打回去
I'll call him back from the car.

530
00:29:48,340 --> 00:29:51,490
听我说  我要告诉你件事  你别慌
Listen to me. What I'm about to say, I don't want you to panic.

531
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:53,150
怎么了
What is it?

532
00:29:56,310 --> 00:30:00,120
日记  邓巴说在她手里
The journal. Dunbar claims she has it.

533
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:03,570
-怎么会  -我不知道
- But how? - I don't know.

534
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:05,340
看来可能是道格
It looks like it might have been Doug.

535
00:30:05,340 --> 00:30:08,880
-他不是...  -我知道  我也难以置信
- He was supposed to-- - I know. It's hard for me to believe.

536
00:30:09,070 --> 00:30:10,590
不  弗兰西斯  这绝不行
No, Francis. This can't happen.

537
00:30:10,590 --> 00:30:12,500
密查姆正在找他
Meechum is tracking him down now.

538
00:30:13,600 --> 00:30:15,200
亲爱的  听我说
Sweetheart, listen to me.

539
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:16,720
不  这件事...这件事
No, the whole thing, it-- The whole thing--

540
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:18,110
她只是威胁了我
All she did was make the threat.

541
00:30:18,110 --> 00:30:19,640
她未必真会那么做
That doesn't mean she actually has it.

542
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:21,930
不论如何  解决这事  弗兰西斯
Whatever you have to do. Just fix it, Francis.

543
00:30:21,940 --> 00:30:23,320
我会的  我保证
I will, I promise you that.

544
00:30:23,320 --> 00:30:25,420
但是现在  你得回来
But in the meantime, you have to come back here.

545
00:30:25,420 --> 00:30:27,950
你得上飞机  你得回来
I need you to get to the plane. You have to come back.

546
00:30:27,950 --> 00:30:31,120
如果我们被奇袭了  我不希望你还在外面
I don't want you there, out on the road, if we get blindsided.

547
00:30:31,980 --> 00:30:34,330
克莱尔  克莱尔
Claire? Claire.

548
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:39,480
我这就回去
I'll come home.

549
00:30:39,890 --> 00:30:42,730
马上登机  就说你不舒服
You go straight to the plane. We'll say you weren't feeling well.

550
00:30:44,320 --> 00:30:45,150
好
Okay.

551
00:30:45,570 --> 00:30:49,890
上帝  让我平静接受我无法改变的事
God, grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change,

552
00:30:50,380 --> 00:30:52,730
让我勇敢改变我可以改变的事
the courage to change the things I can,

553
00:30:53,130 --> 00:30:55,240
并拥有分辨二者的智慧
and the wisdom to know the difference.

554
00:30:55,740 --> 00:30:58,920
坚持来  如果有帮助  就继续努力
Keep coming back. It works if you work it.

555
00:31:20,100 --> 00:31:20,880
怎么样
So?

556
00:31:21,850 --> 00:31:23,900
你还真以为他会喜欢这个吗
You honestly believed he'd go for this?

557
00:31:26,210 --> 00:31:26,990
是啊
Yeah.

558
00:31:27,730 --> 00:31:30,730
内容很好  而且很坦诚
The writing is good. And it's honest.

559
00:31:32,180 --> 00:31:33,840
但哪个神经正常的候选人
But what candidate in their right mind

560
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:35,240
会希望这样的东西发表啊
would want something like this out there?

561
00:31:35,250 --> 00:31:38,290
我要你报导出去  他想扼杀这本书
I need you to write about it. That he's trying to suppress this.

562
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:41,840
-你需要的是睡眠  -帮帮我吧  凯特
- What you need is sleep. - Do this for me, Kate.

563
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:44,290
-不行  这有利益冲突  -得了
- I can't. It's a conflict of interest. - Come on.

564
00:31:44,290 --> 00:31:46,790
我们一上床  就越界了
The moment we slept together, we crossed the line.

565
00:31:46,790 --> 00:31:47,610
去他的界线
Fuck the line!

566
00:31:47,610 --> 00:31:50,980
我不能因为你的书没戏就赌上我的名誉
I'm not risking my reputation because your book is dead.

567
00:31:51,580 --> 00:31:53,370
不  还有戏呢
Oh, no. Not dead.

568
00:31:54,270 --> 00:31:55,220
我会写完的
I'm gonna finish it.

569
00:31:55,220 --> 00:31:57,120
如果有必要  我会改掉名字  当成小说
I'll change the names if I have to, call it fiction.

570
00:31:57,120 --> 00:31:59,370
他是美国总统
He's the President of the United States.

571
00:31:59,370 --> 00:32:01,050
-那又如何  -他能毁掉别人
- So what? - He crushes people.

572
00:32:01,910 --> 00:32:04,880
放手吧  重新开始
Let this go. Just start something new.

573
00:32:07,170 --> 00:32:08,580
"重新开始"
"Start something new."

574
00:32:10,450 --> 00:32:13,380
天呐  你根本不懂
Jesus... Christ, you don't get it.

575
00:32:14,750 --> 00:32:15,840
我经常这样
I do it all the time.

576
00:32:16,510 --> 00:32:19,010
我的编辑毙掉一篇报导  我继续做下一篇
My editor passes on a story, I move on to the next one.

577
00:32:19,010 --> 00:32:21,360
我现在对你太他妈失望了
I'm so fucking disappointed in you right now.

578
00:32:22,150 --> 00:32:22,970
我吗
Me?

579
00:32:23,450 --> 00:32:26,080
我是想把你从幻想中拯救出来
I'm the one trying to save you from your own delusions.

580
00:32:26,080 --> 00:32:27,740
他就是这么说的
That's exactly what he said.

581
00:32:27,790 --> 00:32:28,980
也许他说得对
Maybe he's right.

582
00:32:36,590 --> 00:32:38,850
我都快对你有感情了
I almost felt something for you.

583
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:03,020
进来吧
Come in.

584
00:33:09,650 --> 00:33:10,750
外套给我吧
Let me take your coat.

585
00:33:18,070 --> 00:33:19,570
要给你拿点什么吗  拿点喝的
Can I get you anything? Something to drink?

586
00:33:19,570 --> 00:33:21,590
不不  不用  谢谢
No. No, I'm good. Thanks.

587
00:33:31,180 --> 00:33:33,790
多谢你来我家  但我不会改变主意的
I appreciate the home visit, but I'm not gonna change my mind.

588
00:33:33,790 --> 00:33:35,870
不不  我没觉得你会改主意
No, no. I didn't think you would.

589
00:33:38,330 --> 00:33:39,290
出什么事了吗
Something wrong?

590
00:33:43,060 --> 00:33:44,260
我不知道该怎么做
I don't know what to do.

591
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:46,040
我以为
I figured...

592
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:49,020
我邀你加入竞选时
when I asked you to join the campaign,

593
00:33:49,020 --> 00:33:50,580
我以为你会答应
I just assumed you would say yes.

594
00:33:50,580 --> 00:33:52,730
我们就可以一起工作
That the two of us, we would be working together.

595
00:33:52,730 --> 00:33:53,620
而且
And...

596
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:00,280
我...我
I... I...

597
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:02,770
我无法停止想你
I can't stop thinking about you.

598
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:06,370
你结婚了  杰姬
You're married, Jackie.

599
00:34:09,220 --> 00:34:10,780
因为错误的原因
For the wrong reasons.

600
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:14,520
我以为你们彼此相爱
I thought you loved each other.

601
00:34:15,100 --> 00:34:16,180
不是这种爱
Not like this.

602
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:20,560
我没做我想做的人
I'm not the person I want to be.

603
00:34:20,570 --> 00:34:24,130
你做了你应该做的  看看你的成就
You're who you need to be. Look at what you've achieved.

604
00:34:24,130 --> 00:34:26,330
但你做到了  你彻底放弃了
But you did it. You gave it all up.

605
00:34:26,350 --> 00:34:27,700
毫不犹豫
In a heartbeat.

606
00:34:33,450 --> 00:34:34,680
我们是不同的人
We're different people.

607
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:39,470
你该走了
You should go.

608
00:34:42,860 --> 00:34:44,090
把这些抛在脑后
Put this behind you.

609
00:35:03,140 --> 00:35:05,850
看来以为我们依能保持亲密是我天真了
I guess it was naive to think that we could remain close.

610
00:35:12,890 --> 00:35:14,070
到此为止了吗
So this is it?

611
00:35:16,220 --> 00:35:18,170
是的  到此为止了
Yeah. It is.

612
00:35:24,460 --> 00:35:25,340
杰姬
Jackie?

613
00:35:29,490 --> 00:35:30,360
杰姬
Jackie...

614
00:36:16,030 --> 00:36:17,530
她说在她那儿
She says she has it.

615
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:19,510
她撒谎
She doesn't.

616
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:23,740
我怎么知道没有其它副本
How do I know there aren't other copies?

617
00:36:25,740 --> 00:36:27,220
你的烟放在哪
Where do you keep your cigarettes?

618
00:36:28,430 --> 00:36:29,930
在那上面的碗里
In the bowl up there.

619
00:37:23,070 --> 00:37:25,400
我当初让你销毁时  你为什么不销毁
Why didn't you destroy it when I first asked you to?

620
00:37:25,570 --> 00:37:26,360
不知道
I don't know.

621
00:37:27,860 --> 00:37:31,110
有什么阻止了我  也许有一天我会用到
Something stopped me. Maybe I would need it one day.

622
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:35,110
为了你  证明我的忠诚
For you. To prove my loyalty.

623
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:38,060
你告诉她了  我可没法称之为忠诚
You told her. I'd hardly call that loyalty.

624
00:37:38,060 --> 00:37:39,340
我得向她表明我是认真的
I had to show her I was serious.

625
00:37:39,340 --> 00:37:41,030
这份日记就能证明
The journal was a way to do that.

626
00:37:42,010 --> 00:37:44,430
我从没想过把日记交给她
I never came close to putting it in her possession.

627
00:37:46,890 --> 00:37:48,480
我还要知道什么吗
Anything else I should know?

628
00:37:48,980 --> 00:37:51,510
我戒酒了  已经87天了
I'm sober. It's been 87 days.

629
00:37:51,510 --> 00:37:53,470
我是说关于邓巴
I meant in regards to Dunbar.

630
00:37:53,470 --> 00:37:56,390
这是有关的  现在双方势均力敌
It is related. This is a tight race.

631
00:37:58,090 --> 00:37:59,620
让我做你的幕僚长
Make me your Chief of Staff.

632
00:38:02,250 --> 00:38:03,260
你保证过的
You promised.

633
00:38:03,510 --> 00:38:05,990
你保证等我准备好了  这里会有我一席之地
You promised there'd be a place for me here when I was ready.

634
00:38:05,990 --> 00:38:07,850
那是在你旧瘾复发
That was before you fell off the wagon

635
00:38:07,850 --> 00:38:09,520
拿着日记走进来之前
and walked in here with that journal.

636
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:10,760
我犯过错
I've made mistakes.

637
00:38:10,980 --> 00:38:12,140
我不止一次跌倒
I've fallen down more than once,

638
00:38:12,140 --> 00:38:13,900
而你总会扶我起来
and you've always been there to pick me up.

639
00:38:15,300 --> 00:38:17,440
但过去一年  你也不断跌倒
But you've been falling down for the past year, too,

640
00:38:18,290 --> 00:38:20,260
这次你需要一个人来扶你
and you need someone to pick you up this time.

641
00:38:21,310 --> 00:38:23,940
不是雷米  不是赛斯
It's not Remy. It's not Seth.

642
00:38:24,770 --> 00:38:25,960
是我  弗兰克
It's me, Frank.

643
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:34,200
我怎么知道我能再次信任你呢
And how can I know I can ever trust you again?

644
00:38:36,210 --> 00:38:38,390
因为我刚刚烧掉了两百万美元
Because I just lit two million dollars on fire.

645
00:38:41,290 --> 00:38:44,930
到会人数可能比以往多  在180到220之间
We expect higher than usual turnout, anywhere from 180 to 220.

646
00:38:45,290 --> 00:38:46,500
人越多越好
The higher the turnout, the better.

647
00:38:46,500 --> 00:38:48,450
我们在女性和学生中较受欢迎
We're stronger with women and students.

648
00:38:48,450 --> 00:38:50,440
-我们已争取到...  -抱歉  我得接这通电话
- We've got a GOTV-- - Excuse me, I have to take this.

649
00:38:51,660 --> 00:38:52,540
道格
Doug?

650
00:38:52,810 --> 00:38:54,480
关于日记  我有新消息要告诉你
I have an update regarding the journal.

651
00:38:54,680 --> 00:38:55,510
是什么
What is it?

652
00:38:55,630 --> 00:38:57,320
来自总统的口信
A message from the president.

653
00:39:08,750 --> 00:39:10,820
我只有一件事要说
I have only one thing to say.

654
00:39:12,050 --> 00:39:13,750
去你妈的
Go fuck yourself.

655
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:20,790
天呐  感觉太棒了
Christ, that felt good.

656
00:39:23,280 --> 00:39:24,860
列一份最高法院的
Start putting together a shortlist

657
00:39:24,860 --> 00:39:27,810
人选名单
of potential nominees for the court.

658
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:31,910
你已经...
You already...?

659
00:39:32,900 --> 00:39:34,060
有我呢  先生
I'm on it, sir.

660
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:49,180
克莱尔
Claire.

661
00:39:51,990 --> 00:39:53,070
要我叫楼下厨房
Want me to have them make you something

662
00:39:53,070 --> 00:39:54,570
给你做点什么吗
from the downstairs kitchen?

663
00:39:54,710 --> 00:39:57,380
不用  我在机上吃了  就是有点热
No, I ate on the plane. Just feeling a little warm.

664
00:39:58,190 --> 00:39:59,130
会过去的
It'll pass.

665
00:40:04,020 --> 00:40:05,160
道格怎么说
What did Doug say?

666
00:40:07,770 --> 00:40:08,950
已经销毁了
It's destroyed.

667
00:40:10,030 --> 00:40:12,460
我亲眼看他烧的
I watched him burn the page myself.

668
00:40:13,210 --> 00:40:15,420
-有副本吗  -他说没有
- What about copies? - He says there aren't any.

669
00:40:15,420 --> 00:40:16,580
你信任他吗
And you trust him?

670
00:40:17,230 --> 00:40:20,350
他有的是机会搞破坏  但他没有
He had ample opportunity to do us real damage and he didn't.

671
00:40:20,350 --> 00:40:23,290
-但他留了那么久  -我信他  克莱尔
- But he held onto it for so long-- - I believe him, Claire.

672
00:40:24,300 --> 00:40:25,310
我信他
I believe him.

673
00:40:27,970 --> 00:40:29,910
我要让他做幕僚长
And I'm gonna make him my Chief of Staff.

674
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,700
你疯了吗
Are you out of your mind?

675
00:40:33,700 --> 00:40:36,050
我们需要他  克莱尔  如今更甚以往
We need him, Claire. We need him now more than ever.

676
00:40:36,050 --> 00:40:37,560
他背叛了我们  弗兰西斯
He betrayed us, Francis!

677
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:39,210
他把我的事告诉了邓巴
He told Dunbar about me.

678
00:40:39,210 --> 00:40:41,930
是为了赢得她的信任  不是为了背叛我们
To gain her trust, not betray ours.

679
00:40:41,930 --> 00:40:45,430
听我说  道格是我们一直以来唯一能信任的人
Look, Doug is the only person we've ever been able to trust,

680
00:40:45,430 --> 00:40:47,050
而且他这次手段很高明
and he played this very smart.

681
00:40:47,060 --> 00:40:48,560
他从未真的让我们有危险
He never put us in any real danger.

682
00:40:48,560 --> 00:40:51,130
日记已经销毁  她做不了什么
The journal is gone. She can't do anything.

683
00:40:51,130 --> 00:40:53,190
你让他回来之前  为什么不跟我商量
Why didn't you ask me before you brought him back?

684
00:40:53,190 --> 00:40:56,140
-我们这不在商量吗  -你已经雇了他
- Bec-- We're discussing it now. - After you hired him!

685
00:40:56,140 --> 00:40:58,330
听我说  我知道这事让你很揪心
Look. I know this must have been harrowing for you,

686
00:40:58,330 --> 00:41:00,180
-但听我说  都结束了  -不  我不...
- but listen, it is ov-- - No. I don't--

687
00:41:00,980 --> 00:41:03,150
我开始质疑一切了  弗兰西斯
I'm starting to question all of it, Francis.

688
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:08,130
这一切究竟有什么意义  我们这么做是为了什么
What any of it is worth. What... what are we doing this for?

689
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:10,390
为了这栋房子
For this house.

690
00:41:10,900 --> 00:41:12,750
为了总统之位
For the presidency.

691
00:41:14,300 --> 00:41:16,980
听我说  如果你需要休息几天  那没什么
Now, look, if you need to take a few days off, that's fine.

692
00:41:16,980 --> 00:41:19,430
你明天不用跟我去爱荷华州
You do not have to come with me to Iowa tomorrow.

693
00:41:22,300 --> 00:41:24,770
不  我当然要去
No. Of course, I'll be there.

694
00:41:35,630 --> 00:41:38,660
欢迎回来  道格  恭喜了
Welcome back, Doug. Congratulations.

695
00:41:39,440 --> 00:41:40,220
谢谢
Thank you.

696
00:41:40,630 --> 00:41:41,780
我只想问下你打算
I just wanted to get a heads up on

697
00:41:41,780 --> 00:41:43,530
什么时候正式宣布
when you'd like to make the formal announcement.

698
00:41:43,830 --> 00:41:45,360
党团会议之后吧
Let's do it after the caucus.

699
00:41:45,360 --> 00:41:47,450
不要让大家的注意力偏离竞选
I don't want to draw any attention away from the campaign.

700
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:50,010
那你今天别参加新闻发布会了
You probably shouldn't attend the press briefing today.

701
00:41:50,150 --> 00:41:51,980
嗯  我会在那之前走的
No. I'll take off before then.

702
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:53,170
给  你该看看
Here, you should see this.

703
00:41:55,300 --> 00:41:56,570
10分钟前曝出的
This just came out ten minutes ago.

704
00:41:56,770 --> 00:41:59,180
{\pos(95.4,71.55)}证据增加  美军海豹突击队
参与约旦河谷行动

705
00:42:00,630 --> 00:42:01,760
你给总统看了吗
Have you shown the president?

706
00:42:01,770 --> 00:42:03,130
我起草了讲话要点
I drafted up some talking points.

707
00:42:03,140 --> 00:42:04,450
我觉得你会想去跟他说
I figured you'd want to brief him.

708
00:42:04,950 --> 00:42:05,980
我回办公室了
I'll be in my office.

709
00:42:07,530 --> 00:42:08,430
赛斯
Seth.

710
00:42:11,390 --> 00:42:13,120
总统告诉我你也想做这工作
The president told me you asked for the job.

711
00:42:15,580 --> 00:42:17,590
我当时不知道你也有这打算
Yeah, I didn't realize that you were in contention.

712
00:42:18,110 --> 00:42:19,470
我不希望你怨我
I don't want you to resent me.

713
00:42:20,350 --> 00:42:21,920
我是专业人士的
Hey, I'm a professional.

714
00:42:22,940 --> 00:42:25,410
你如果要改讲话要点告诉我
Let me know if you want any changes made to the talking points.

715
00:42:26,120 --> 00:42:27,190
肯定写的很好
I'm sure they're good.

716
00:42:28,410 --> 00:42:29,830
拿去给总统吧
You can share 'em with the president.

717
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,060
你不要先过目吗
You don't want to look 'em over first?

718
00:42:33,720 --> 00:42:36,350
不用  我相信你
No. I trust your judgment.

719
00:42:48,350 --> 00:42:50,330
我可以告诉大家  名单正在筹办
I can tell you that the shortlist is coming along,

720
00:42:50,330 --> 00:42:52,600
我有意在接下来两三周里
and it is my intention to nominate someone

721
00:42:52,730 --> 00:42:54,810
就做出提名
within the next two or three weeks.

722
00:42:54,810 --> 00:42:57,440
我们一定要行动快
It's very important that we do this quickly,

723
00:42:57,640 --> 00:43:00,540
让参议院有时间进行听证
so that the Senate has time for their hearings.

724
00:43:00,540 --> 00:43:03,350
这个位置本来也不好空太久
And we shouldn't leave that seat empty too long anyway,

725
00:43:03,360 --> 00:43:05,120
法庭还要继续运行
while the Court is still in session.

726
00:43:05,360 --> 00:43:06,990
-总统  -萨拉
- Mr. President? - Sara.

727
00:43:07,310 --> 00:43:09,980
总统先生  您能就鲍德温女士关于
Mr. President, would you comment on Ms. Baldwin's article

728
00:43:09,980 --> 00:43:11,680
约旦河谷行动的文章做下评论吗
about the Jordan Valley operation?

729
00:43:11,680 --> 00:43:13,020
我觉得鲍德温女士的文章
I think Ms. Baldwin's article

730
00:43:13,020 --> 00:43:14,720
不过是臆测
is really nothing more than speculation.

731
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:16,290
-但是证据  -什么
- But the evidence... - I'm sorry?

732
00:43:16,290 --> 00:43:18,470
但她提出的证据很有说服力
But the evidence she presents is convincing.

733
00:43:19,730 --> 00:43:21,930
证据  一封信吗
Evidence? A letter?

734
00:43:22,620 --> 00:43:24,690
很遗憾  我虽不愿意
Unfortunately, I have to write letters like that

735
00:43:24,690 --> 00:43:26,170
却不得不常写这种信
more often than I would like.

736
00:43:26,490 --> 00:43:28,710
我觉得这仅仅能证明
And I don't think it's proof of anything more than

737
00:43:28,940 --> 00:43:30,970
我曾写信给一个为国捐躯的
I reached out to the family of a young man

738
00:43:31,370 --> 00:43:33,540
年轻人的家人
who sacrificed his life for our country

739
00:43:33,540 --> 00:43:35,680
以及我对此永远充满谢意
and for which I am eternally grateful.

740
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:37,250
总统先生
Mr. President?

741
00:43:37,250 --> 00:43:39,610
鲍德温女士  我们讨论的是你的文章
Well, Ms. Baldwin, it is your article we're discussing.

742
00:43:39,610 --> 00:43:41,220
我想如果我不让你提问
I suppose I'd get hammered

743
00:43:41,220 --> 00:43:42,940
恐怕会挨批评
if I didn't allow you to ask a question.

744
00:43:42,940 --> 00:43:45,590
谢谢  总统先生  我的问题很简单
Thank you, Mr. President. My question is very straightforward.

745
00:43:45,600 --> 00:43:46,590
您在信中提到
You mentioned in the letter

746
00:43:46,590 --> 00:43:49,140
尼可斯中尉在演练中丧命
that Lieutenant Nix died in a training exercise.

747
00:43:49,140 --> 00:43:50,800
您亲自在信上签名
You signed this letter with your own hand.

748
00:43:50,800 --> 00:43:53,620
您能如实告诉我们他是这么死的吗
Can you tell us in all honesty that this is how he died?

749
00:43:53,850 --> 00:43:54,800
我要告诉你
I can tell you that

750
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:57,500
这就是五角大楼向我报告的情况
this is exactly what the Pentagon reported to me.

751
00:43:57,840 --> 00:44:00,480
除此之外  政府和国防部
And beyond that, it's not the policy of this administration

752
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:03,400
都不会讨论关于特种部队士兵
or the Department of Defense to discuss any specifics

753
00:44:03,400 --> 00:44:05,270
死亡的详细情况
about any Special Forces deaths.

754
00:44:05,270 --> 00:44:06,330
我能再问一个问题吗
May I ask one more, please?

755
00:44:06,340 --> 00:44:08,110
我想这个话题已经讨论完了
I believe we're finished with that subject now.

756
00:44:08,110 --> 00:44:09,240
是关于爱荷华
It's about Iowa.

757
00:44:10,310 --> 00:44:11,310
好吧  问吧
Yes, all right. Go ahead.

758
00:44:11,310 --> 00:44:13,210
您妻子出席了多场竞选活动
Your wife has been doing a lot of events.

759
00:44:13,300 --> 00:44:15,460
她辞去在联合国的职位
Did she resign her post at the United Nations

760
00:44:15,460 --> 00:44:18,300
是因为您觉得她作为竞选筹码
because you think she's more valuable as a campaign asset

761
00:44:18,300 --> 00:44:19,310
比当大使更有价值吗
than an ambassador?

762
00:44:19,430 --> 00:44:22,030
克莱尔确实出席了很多活动  这是事实
Claire has been doing a lot of events, that is true,

763
00:44:22,030 --> 00:44:24,680
跟她以前参与我的每场竞选一样
as she has in every campaign that I have ever run.

764
00:44:24,740 --> 00:44:28,060
我想我的策略是希望美国人民
I'm hoping, I suppose my strategy is that if the American people

765
00:44:28,060 --> 00:44:29,360
看到我能凭聪明才智
can see that I was smart enough

766
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:31,360
娶到像克莱尔这样出色的女人
to marry an extraordinary woman like Claire,

767
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:32,750
他们或许会认为我也有
well, they might think I'm smart enough

768
00:44:32,750 --> 00:44:34,630
当美国总统的脑子
to be President of the United States.

769
00:44:34,900 --> 00:44:35,970
至于大使的事
As for the ambassadorship,

770
00:44:35,970 --> 00:44:38,480
那完全是她的决定  不是我的
that was entirely her decision, not mine.

771
00:44:38,480 --> 00:44:41,420
她喜欢竞选宣传  我也希望能今天稍后能
She enjoys campaigning, and I'm looking forward to getting back

772
00:44:41,420 --> 00:44:43,290
回到爱荷华州陪伴她
to Iowa with her a little later today.

773
00:44:43,900 --> 00:44:45,210
非常感谢各位
Thank you all very much.

774
00:44:49,370 --> 00:44:51,030
我们知道他在加拉加斯[委瑞内拉首都]附近
We know he's somewhere near Caracas.

775
00:44:51,030 --> 00:44:52,190
我需要找他回来
I need him back.

776
00:44:52,830 --> 00:44:54,750
委瑞内拉方面不太配合
The Venezuelans haven't been cooperating.

777
00:44:55,020 --> 00:44:56,470
我们有引渡令
We have extradition.

778
00:44:56,700 --> 00:44:58,010
不代表他们会执行
Doesn't mean they'll enforce.

779
00:45:01,180 --> 00:45:02,800
那就给我个准确地址
Then get me a precise location.

780
00:45:02,800 --> 00:45:03,560
为什么
Why?

781
00:45:04,290 --> 00:45:05,270
这跟你没关系
It doesn't concern you.

782
00:45:05,270 --> 00:45:06,660
跟我有关  局里很多人
It does concern me. There are a lot of people

783
00:45:06,660 --> 00:45:08,070
因为他的偷偷离境
at the agency who are embarrassed that

784
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:10,010
而丢了人
he crossed the border without us knowing.

785
00:45:10,550 --> 00:45:11,830
那不是我的错
That's not my problem.

786
00:45:12,070 --> 00:45:15,110
是你吗  护照解锁
Was it you? Passport lock?

787
00:45:16,870 --> 00:45:19,490
能办到这事的再就只有国安部
The only other agency that could've lifted it is Homeland.

788
00:45:19,730 --> 00:45:21,000
我知道你那里有朋友
I know you have friends there.

789
00:45:21,000 --> 00:45:22,390
我到处都有朋友
I have friends everywhere.

790
00:45:23,120 --> 00:45:25,450
我不会帮你擦屁股的  道格
I'm not gonna help you clean up your mess, Doug.

791
00:45:26,100 --> 00:45:27,890
如果是你帮他出逃的话
Not if you helped him escape.

792
00:45:28,670 --> 00:45:30,060
这不是请求
This isn't a request.

793
00:45:30,710 --> 00:45:32,830
我现在是总统的幕僚长
I'm Chief of Staff to the president now.

794
00:45:33,600 --> 00:45:35,600
-他还没宣布呢  -他会的
- He hasn't announced anyone. - He will.

795
00:45:36,150 --> 00:45:37,740
如果你希望我的第一项正式工作
And if you want my first official task

796
00:45:37,740 --> 00:45:39,910
就是找人代替你  那行啊
to be finding your replacement, so be it.

797
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:43,420
否则  就告诉我嘉文在哪
If not, you tell me where Gavin is.

798
00:45:51,630 --> 00:45:53,810
我今早看了新闻发布会
I watched the press conference this morning.

799
00:45:54,080 --> 00:45:56,310
我觉得鲍德温的文章会被淡忘的
I think the Baldwin article will blow over.

800
00:45:56,600 --> 00:45:58,710
毫无力量  站不住脚
A non-story. No legs.

801
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:00,920
你说是我决定辞职的
You said it was my decision to resign.

802
00:46:01,680 --> 00:46:02,680
确实是啊  不是吗
Well, it was, wasn't it?

803
00:46:02,680 --> 00:46:04,570
至少我们是这样表现的
I mean, at least that's how we presented it.

804
00:46:09,510 --> 00:46:12,210
我昨天在爱荷华跟一个女人聊天
I spoke with a woman yesterday in Iowa, who...

805
00:46:13,490 --> 00:46:15,430
她说她不会支持我们
said she couldn't support us...

806
00:46:16,580 --> 00:46:17,990
因为她不信任你
because she doesn't trust you.

807
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:21,950
我又不是第一个不被一些人信任的政客
Well, I'm not the first politician that some people don't trust.

808
00:46:21,950 --> 00:46:24,110
我们已经撒谎很长时间了  弗兰西斯
We've been lying for a long time, Francis.

809
00:46:24,110 --> 00:46:26,160
当然  想想如果我们开始说出真相
Of course we have. Imagine what the voters would think

810
00:46:26,160 --> 00:46:27,720
选民会怎么想
if we started telling the truth.

811
00:46:28,480 --> 00:46:29,510
不是对选民
Not to them.

812
00:46:31,810 --> 00:46:32,800
是对彼此
To each other.

813
00:46:39,470 --> 00:46:49,470
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}提名最高法院法官  往往是一名美国总统任内最重要的工作之一
由于美国最高法院法官是终身制
一旦获得任命  大法官就可以一直工作下去
一名总统最多只能在白宫发号施令8年
他所提名的大法官却可以在最高法院影响美国社会长达几十年
在寻找合适人选时  总统们会选择同自己政见相似的候选人
但是由于任职后没有选举压力
大法官们在判案时并不见得总会站在自己所属的党派一边
小布什总统在离任前提名共和党人约翰·罗伯兹为最高法院首席大法官
但是当民主党总统奥巴马的《医疗保险改革法案》遇到麻烦时
罗伯兹却把自己关键的一票投给了支持奥巴马的一方

814
00:47:04,470 --> 00:47:14,470
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}目前在任的九名大法官中
已经82岁高龄的民主党人露丝·金士堡是年龄最长的一位
金士堡曾两次罹患癌症  虽然都已治愈  但是健康状况欠佳
许多民主党人都在劝她尽快退休
这样现任总统奥巴马就有机会提名一位民主党法官来取代她
一旦民主党在2016年大选中失手  被共和党人占了白宫
而金士堡在2016年后退休  就会被一名共和党人取而代之
打破最高法院现有的平衡
但是倔强的金士堡拒绝听取这些劝退的意见
她总是回答说  奥巴马不可能找到比我更好的人选
在过去连续两年的国情咨文演讲中  奥巴马在台上口若悬河
坐在台下的金士堡却在打盹儿
不久前她在接受访问时承认  今年参加国情咨文前
跟最高法院几位法官同僚喝了几杯  才会在会场上忍不住打盹儿

